    <p>For Maryland's climate, HVAC systems should have minimum SEER ratings of 14-16, though higher efficiency units with SEER 18+ ratings provide better long-term value due to the state's high electricity costs and extended cooling seasons. Heat pumps with HSPF ratings of 8.5 or higher are recommended for heating efficiency. The optimal SEER rating depends on home size, insulation levels, and individual usage patterns, but most Maryland homeowners benefit from investing in higher efficiency equipment due to substantial annual runtime hours.</p>
  </div>
  
